The paper focuses on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in computer vision tasks by promoting compositional representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for training CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). The method involves encouraging networks to form representations that disentangle objects from their surroundings and from each other, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of activation functions and loss functions, which are common topics in neural networks (cs.NE - Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method in object recognition tasks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL - Computation and Language).
